=== 2.6 Logarithm and Exponential

The natural logarithm stem:[\ln x] is the inverse of stem:[e^x]:

stem:[e^{\ln x} = x \quad \text{and} \quad \ln(e^x) = x]

Key identities:

- stem:[\ln(ab) = \ln a + \ln b]
- stem:[\ln(a^n) = n \ln a]
- stem:[\ln(1) = 0], stem:[\ln(e) = 1]

In GPT, the cross-entropy loss uses stem:[\ln p] where stem:[p] is a probability (Chapter 11).
Because stem:[p \in (0, 1\]], stem:[\ln p \leq 0] — the log-loss is always non-negative.

==== Scheme Implementation

[source,scheme]
----
(define (log-base-e x)
  (log x))

(define (safe-log x)
  (if (<= x 0)
      -inf.0
      (log x)))
----

==== Example

stem:[\ln(1) = 0], stem:[\ln(e) \approx 1], stem:[\ln(0.5) \approx -0.693], stem:[\ln(0.1) \approx -2.303]

This is why low-probability predictions incur high loss: stem:[\ln(0.01) = -4.605].

[source,scheme]
----
(display (log 1))       ; => 0
(display (log (exp 1))) ; => 1.0
(display (log 0.5))     ; => -0.6931...
(display (log 0.1))     ; => -2.3025...
----
